[{"id":"VR803188","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows three identical blocks labeled A, B, and C. Block A has a temperature of 300 kelvin. Block B has a temperature of 250 kelvin. Block C has a temperature 450 kelvin. The blocks are in a row (from left to right, A, B, and C) and are touching. The blocks are insulated from their environment.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR803188.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Blocks <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math></span></span>, and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C\"><math alttext=\"C\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math></span></span> are made of the same material, and have identical sizes, shapes, and masses. Blocks <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math></span></span>, and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C\"><math alttext=\"C\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math></span></span> are initially at temperatures of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"300 kelvin\"><math alttext=\"300 kelvin\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>300</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"250 kelvin\"><math alttext=\"250 kelvin\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>250</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>K</mtext></math></span></span>, and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"450 kelvin\"><math alttext=\"450 kelvin\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>450</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>K</mtext></math></span></span> when the blocks are placed in direct contact with each other and isolated from their surroundings, as shown. The three-block system eventually reaches thermal equilibrium. Which of the following correctly describes the change, if any, in the entropy of the three-block system?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR803188_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The entropy is constant.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The entropy decreases until it reaches a constant value.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The entropy increases until it reaches a constant value.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The entropy change cannot be known without knowing the initial entropies of each individual block.</p>"],"answer":2}]